.TH "t3_load_mtus" 9 "t3_load_mtus" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t3_load_mtus \- write the MTU and congestion control HW tables
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" t3_load_mtus
.BI "(struct adapter *adap "  ","
.BI "unsigned short mtus[NMTUS] "  ","
.BI "unsigned short alpha[NCCTRL_WIN] "  ","
.BI "unsigned short beta[NCCTRL_WIN] "  ","
.BI "unsigned short mtu_cap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adap" 12
the adapter
.IP "mtus" 12
the unrestricted values for the MTU table
.IP "alpha" 12
the values for the congestion control alpha parameter
.IP "beta" 12
the values for the congestion control beta parameter
.IP "mtu_cap" 12
the maximum permitted effective MTU

Write the MTU table with the supplied MTUs capping each at \fImtu_cap\fP.
Update the high-speed congestion control table with the supplied alpha,
beta, and MTUs.
